thread.title: H.S. football: Huge third quarter leads Waldwick/Midland Park over Lodi, 29-21
thread.title_full: H.S. football: Huge third quarter leads Waldwick/Midland Park over Lodi, 29-21

title: H.S. football: Huge third quarter leads Waldwick/Midland Park over Lodi, 29-21
text:
Buy this photo DAVID FIGUEIRA/SPECIAL TO THE RECORD West Milford quarterback Anthony Hanratty threw for 241 yards and two touchdowns in the Highlanders’ overtime win over Passaic Valley on Saturday. 
LODI — Waldwick/Midland Park, No. 18 in The Record public school Top 20, scored 16 unanswered points in the third quarter Saturday to post a 29-21 come-from-behind victory over Lodi in NJIC Colonial Division football action. 
Sonny DiPasquale and Garret King each scored in the third quarter for the Warriors. DiPasquale scored two touchdowns and senior defensive lineman Zach Van Kat returned a first-quarter fumble 34 yards for a touchdown. 
Quarterback Steven Villa had another strong game for the Rams, carrying 18 times for 260 yards and three touchdowns. 
RUTHERFORD 49, MANCHESTER 14 (at Rutherford): Junior running back Kevin Kosakowski rushed for 141 yards and two touchdowns to lead the No. 15 Bulldogs to a win in Colonial Division play. 
The Bulldogs outscored the Falcons, 38-0, in the second half. Quarterback Nick Birchby threw for 153 yards and three touchdowns, and the Rutherford defense forced six turnovers. 
PASSAIC TECH 43, FAIR LAWN 6 (at Fair Lawn): Quarterback Derrick Cuavers threw for 202 yards and two touchdowns and rushed for another to power the No. 4 Bulldogs to a Big North Liberty Division win. 
Kevin Cooper carried 11 times for 90 yards and two touchdowns, and caught two passes for 53 yards and a touchdown. Isaiah Tolbert led the PCT defense with six tackles, two for loss. 
BUTLER 14, MORRIS CATHOLIC 7, OT (at Denville): Sean Mefford scored his second touchdown of the game in overtime to give the Bulldogs an NJAC Liberty Division victory. 
Quarterback Domenic Gentile threw for 244 yards and a first-quarter TD pass to Mefford. Danny Polons had an interception in the end zone to end the game. 
DUMONT 28, CLIFFSIDE PARK 0 (at Dumont): Skylar Marino rushed for 100 yards and two touchdowns to lift the Huskies to a Big North American Division win. Quarterback Matt Monteverde threw for 120 yards and touchdown and ran for another. 
WEST MILFORD 17, PASSAIC VALLEY 14, OT (at Little Falls): Anthony Pellegrino booted a 32-yard field goal in overtime as the Highlanders snapped a three- game losing streak in Big North Independence Division action. 
West Milford quarterback Anthony Hanratty threw for 241 yards and two touchdowns, including a 21-yard touchdown to Austin Hopler in the fourth quarter that sent the game into overtime. It was Hopler’s second touchdown catch of the game. 
HARRISON 54, IMMACULATE CONCEPTION 6 (at Harrison): Michael O’Donnell scored three touchdowns, including one on a 98-yard run, to help the Blue Tide snap a four-game losing streak in a non-league game. © 2015 North Jersey Media Group Tags:
